Creating an archive using tar command

at the command line, in the folder with the all the files you want to tar

tar cvzf archive_name.tar.gz *  //will tar up all file in folder

for specifing files

tar cvzf archive_name.tar.gz name_of_new_zipped_file file1.cpp file1.h main.cpp

What the flags mean
c – create a new archive
t - view archive titles
x - extract
v – verbosely list files which are processed.
z- filter the archive through gzip
f – following is the archive file name
* - all files in this directory


Viewing the files in your tar

 tar tvfz archive_name.tar.gz



Extracting files from a tar

tar xvfz archive_name.tar.gz



















